it would be a hyperbola.

1412
00:55:40,194 --> 00:55:41,354
With two of them,

1413
00:55:41,354 --> 00:55:42,714
it becomes a hyperboloid.

1414
00:55:42,834 --> 00:55:44,494
And here's what the hyperboloid looks like.

1415
00:55:46,894 --> 00:55:48,174
Plot t upward,

1416
00:55:48,174 --> 00:55:50,074
x and y horizontally.

1417
00:55:50,614 --> 00:55:51,094
Oops,

1418
00:55:51,094 --> 00:55:52,174
not so good over here.

1419
00:55:52,494 --> 00:55:54,594
And now draw a cone.

1420
00:55:59,034 --> 00:56:00,834
We're not really doing relativity,

1421
00:56:00,834 --> 00:56:02,994
but it looks an awful lot like relativity.

1422
00:56:03,374 --> 00:56:06,274
But this is just a trick for drawing a surface.

1423
00:56:07,074 --> 00:56:08,134
Draw a cone.

1424
00:56:08,434 --> 00:56:08,714
Whoops,

1425
00:56:08,714 --> 00:56:09,934
that's not a very good cone.

1426
00:56:18,854 --> 00:56:20,294
It's a right angle cone,

1427
00:56:20,594 --> 00:56:22,934
and it corresponds to the surface t squared

1428
00:56:22,934 --> 00:56:25,274
minus x squared minus y squared equals what?

1429
00:56:27,154 --> 00:56:28,094
For a cone.

1430
00:56:29,274 --> 00:56:29,834
Zero.

1431
00:56:31,153 --> 00:56:33,634
t squared equals x squared plus y squared.

1432
00:56:34,234 --> 00:56:34,914
That's a cone.

1433
00:56:35,154 --> 00:56:36,274
It's not a hyperboloid.

1434
00:56:36,634 --> 00:56:38,114
But now put a one there.

1435
00:56:38,754 --> 00:56:39,014
Well,

1436
00:56:39,014 --> 00:56:39,414
let's see.

1437
00:56:39,454 --> 00:56:40,014
First of all,

1438
00:56:40,014 --> 00:56:42,754
set x and y equals zero.

1439
00:56:42,894 --> 00:56:44,454
Let's go on to the t axis.

1440
00:56:44,714 --> 00:56:46,664
Here's the vertical t axis that

1441
00:56:46,664 --> 00:56:48,614
corresponds to x and y equals zero.

1442
00:56:49,374 --> 00:56:51,654
Where is the point t squared equals one?

1443
00:56:51,994 --> 00:56:52,434
Well,

1444
00:56:52,434 --> 00:56:53,774
that's just a point t equals one.

1445
00:56:54,154 --> 00:56:55,114
There are two of them,

1446
00:56:55,114 --> 00:56:56,394
one on the top and one on the bottom,

1447
00:56:56,454 --> 00:56:58,034
but let's just concentrate on the top one.

1448
00:56:58,114 --> 00:56:58,574
That's over here.

1449
00:56:59,114 --> 00:57:00,094
t equals one.

1450
00:57:00,094 --> 00:57:03,774
What happens as you move away from that point?

1451
00:57:03,974 --> 00:57:05,714
You form a hyperboloid.

1452
00:57:05,894 --> 00:57:08,914
A hyperboloid of revolution.

1453
00:57:09,474 --> 00:57:12,314
A round hyperboloid of revolution.

1454
00:57:18,794 --> 00:57:19,814
Like so.

1455
00:57:23,694 --> 00:57:24,534
Now,

1456
00:57:24,534 --> 00:57:24,614
I'm going to take a look at this.

1457
00:57:24,614 --> 00:57:24,614
Now,

1458
00:57:24,614 --> 00:57:31,014
it does not look like every point on this hyperboloid

1459
00:57:31,014 --> 00:57:32,414
is the same as every other point.

1460
00:57:32,634 --> 00:57:34,974
It really looks like this one is special.

1461
00:57:35,174 --> 00:57:35,834
But it's not.

1462
00:57:35,914 --> 00:57:40,054
If you use the metric,

1463
00:57:42,434 --> 00:57:46,374
not dt squared plus dx squared plus dy squared,

1464
00:57:46,634 --> 00:57:48,694
but you measure distances on here

1465
00:57:49,314 --> 00:57:53,154
as dt squared minus dx squared minus dy squared.

1466
00:57:53,534 --> 00:57:54,134
Sorry.

1467
00:57:54,134 --> 00:57:57,634
The x squared plus dy squared minus dt squared.

1468
00:57:58,074 --> 00:58:00,114
You measure distances on here

1469
00:58:01,834 --> 00:58:04,434
using the relativistic metric,

1470
00:58:04,694 --> 00:58:06,494
pretending that this was time.

1471
00:58:06,934 --> 00:58:07,774
It's not time.

1472
00:58:07,914 --> 00:58:11,414
It's just an embedding space to draw a hyperboloid.

1473
00:58:12,514 --> 00:58:14,934
If you do things that way,

1474
00:58:15,814 --> 00:58:19,414
then this hyperboloid is absolutely uniform.

1475
00:58:19,914 --> 00:58:20,914
How do I know it?

1476
00:58:21,194 --> 00:58:23,894
Because to go from one point to another point

1477
00:58:23,894 --> 00:58:27,174
on the hyperboloid is equivalent to a Lorentz transformation

1478
00:58:27,174 --> 00:58:30,014
which moves the time axis in various ways.

1479
00:58:30,874 --> 00:58:33,494
But if you're not comfortable with that,

1480
00:58:33,594 --> 00:58:36,634
we'll just take it as a true fact

1481
00:58:36,634 --> 00:58:37,994
that the hyperboloid,

1482
00:58:38,474 --> 00:58:40,094
when distances are measured

1483
00:58:40,914 --> 00:58:42,174
with the metric,

1484
00:58:42,314 --> 00:58:45,134
the x squared plus dy squared minus dt squared,

1485
00:58:45,534 --> 00:58:49,414
then this hyperboloid really is completely uniform.

1486
00:58:49,874 --> 00:58:53,494
And now supposing I want to stereographically project it.

1487
00:58:54,013 --> 00:58:57,014
Here's a way to stereographically project it that's useful.

1488
00:58:57,634 --> 00:58:58,114
Again,

1489
00:58:58,114 --> 00:58:59,614
you draw a tangent plane.

1490
00:59:00,174 --> 00:59:01,694
A tangent plane now

1491
00:59:06,814 --> 00:59:09,334
is tangent to the bottom point.

1492
00:59:09,574 --> 00:59:12,434
Think of us as living at the bottom point here.

1493
00:59:13,814 --> 00:59:15,254
We live at the bottom point.

1494
00:59:15,474 --> 00:59:17,054
And we look out around us.

1495
00:59:17,374 --> 00:59:19,314
We look out to given distances.

1496
00:59:19,594 --> 00:59:20,434
Distance out here,

1497
00:59:20,434 --> 00:59:21,294
distance out here.

1498
00:59:22,134 --> 00:59:23,254
But now we're going to take

1499
00:59:23,494 --> 00:59:25,514
every point on the green hyperboloid

1500
00:59:26,394 --> 00:59:29,114
and map it to a point on the blue plane.

